539-cebu-flight-ban-legazpi-clark-cagayan-de-oro-dumaguete-coronavirus</ref> [[Godofredo P. Ramos Airport|Caticlan]],<ref name=\"gma\">https://www.gmanetwork.com/news/serbisyopubliko/transportation/729780/carriers-cancel-cebu-flights-amid-travel-ban/story/</ref> [[Clark International Airport|Clark]],<ref name=\"rappler\"/> [[Francisco Bangoy International Airport|Davao]],<ref name=\"gma\"/> [[General Santos International Airport|General Santos]], [[Kalibo International Airport|Kalibo]],<ref name=\"gma\"/> [[Kaohsiung International Airport|Kaohsiung]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Liu |first1=Jim |title=Philippines AirAsia expands Cebu international service from Aug 2019 |url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/284397/philippines-airasia-expands-cebu-international-service-from-aug-2019/ |website=Routesonline |accessdate=17 May 2019}}</ref> [[Kuala Lumpur International Airport|Kuala Lumpur\u2013International]], [[Macau International Airport|Macau]], [[Ninoy Aquino International Airport|Manila]],<ref name=\"gma\"/> [[Puerto Princesa International Airport|Puerto Princesa]],<ref name=\"gma\"/> [[Incheon International Airport|Seoul\u2013Incheon]], [[Shenzhen Bao'an International Airport|Shenzhen]], [[Singapore Changi Airport|Singapore]], [[Taiwan Taoyuan International Airport|Taipei\u2013Taoyuan]], [[Zamboanga International Airport|Zamboanga]]<ref>https://www.facebook.com/AirAsia.Zam/photos/a.111748950407299/112848646963996/</ref><ref name=\"CEB_Ban_20\" />\n<!-- -->\n| [[Qatar Airways]] | [[Hamad International Airport|Doha]] (resumes 1 July 2020)<ref>https://www.qatarairways.com/en/press-releases/2020/January/KAS2020.html?activeTag=Press-releases</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Liu |first1=Jim |title=Qatar Airways NS20 Network changes as of 19MAR20 |url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/290366/qatar-airways-ns20-network-changes-as-of-19mar20/ |website=Routesonline |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n|[[Royal Air Charter|Royal Air Philippines]]