 freedom (consecutive cabotage)|eighth freedom]] traffic rights to transport passengers solely from Cebu to Clark.</small>\n\n===Cargo===\n{{Airport-dest-list\n<!-- -->\n| [[Air Hong Kong]] | [[Hong Kong International Airport|Hong Kong]]\n| [[FedEx Express]] | [[Guangzhou Baiyun International Airport|Guangzhou]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Tri-MG Intra Asia Airlines]] | [[Hong Kong International Airport|Hong Kong]]\n<!-- -->\n}}\n\n==Statistics==\n[[File:Cebu (Lapu-Lapu) - Mactan International (Gen Benito Ebuen AB) (CEB - RPVM) AN2322561.jpg|thumb|280px|right|Terminal 1's departure waiting area.]]\n[[File:Cebu (Lapu-Lapu) - Mactan International (Gen Benito Ebuen AB) (CEB - RPVM) AN2256521.jpg|280px|thumb|right| Exterior of Terminal 1]]\nData from Mactan\u2013Cebu International Airport Authority (MCIAA).<ref>{{cite web |title=GRAPHS \u2013 Mactan \u2013 Cebu International Airport Authority |url=http://mciaa.gov.ph/index.php/graphs/ |accessdate=12 January 2019}}</ref>\n<ref>http://mciaa.gov.ph/statistics/ |accessdate=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Passenger movements===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 85%\"\n|-\n! Year !! Domestic !! International !! Total !! Change\n|-\n! 1991\n| 1,401,671 || 57,988 || '''1,459,659''' || {{steady}}\n|-\n! 1992\n| 1,592,173 || 97,842 || '''1,690,015''' || {{increase}} 15.78%\n|-\n! 1993\n| 1,635,779 || 172,966 || '''1,808,745''' || {{increase}} 7.03%\n|-\n! 1994\n| 1,714,104 || 244,602 || '''1,958,706''' || {{increase}} 8.29%\n|-\n! 1995\n| 1,841,904 || 307,203 || '''2,149,107''' || {{increase}} 9.72%\n|-\n! 1996\n| 2,047,966 || 354,818 || '''2,402,784''' || {{increase}} 11.80%\n|-\n! 1997\n| 2,331,431 || 387,190 || '''2,718,621''' || {{increase}} 13.14%\n|-\n! 1998\n| 1,759,141 || 312,663 || '''2,071,804''' || {{decrease}} 23.79%\n|-\n! 1999\n| 1,912,107 || 384,047 || '''2,296,154''' || {{increase}} 10.83%\n|-\n! 2000\n| 1,889,114 || 403,735 || '''2,292,849''' || {{decrease}} 0.14%\n|-\n! 2001\n| 1,855,363 || 397,370 || '''2,25