inthia]] and [[Duke of Carniola|Carniola]]<br>[[Count of Tyrol]] | years=1519\u20131521 }}\n{{S-aft | rows=3 | after=[[Ferdinand I, Holy Roman Emperor|Ferdinand I]]}}\n{{S-ttl | rows=1 | title=[[King of Germany]] | years=1519\u20131556 }}\n{{S-break}}\n{{S-ttl | rows=1 | title=[[Holy Roman Emperor]]<br>[[King of Italy]]| years=1530\u20131556}}\n{{S-break}}\n{{S-roy|es}}\n|-\n{{S-bef|rows=2|before=[[Joanna of Castile|Joanna]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Prince of Asturias]]|years=1504\u20131516}}\n{{S-vac|rows=2|next=[[Philip II of Spain|Philip (II)]]}}\n|-\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Prince of Girona]]|years=1516}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Monarchs of Spain}}\n{{Spanish Empire}}\n{{Holy Roman Emperors}}\n{{German monarchs}}\n{{Monarchs of Luxembourg}}\n{{Princes of Asturias}}\n{{Austrian archdukes}}\n{{Infantes of Aragon}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Charles 05, Holy Roman Emperor}}\n[[Category:Charles V, Holy Roman Emperor| ]]\n[[Category:1500 births]]\n[[Category:1558 deaths]]\n[[Category:16th-century Aragonese monarchs]]\n[[Category:16th-century Castilian monarchs]]\n[[Category:16th-century Holy Roman Emperors]]\n[[Category:16th-century House of Habsburg]]\n[[Category:16th-century Kings of Sicily]]\n[[Category:16th-century Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:16th-century rulers of Austria]]\n[[Category:16th-century Spanish monarchs]]\n[[Category:Aragonese infantes]]\n[[Category:Archdukes of Austria]]\n[[Category:Burials in the Pantheon of Kings at El Escorial]]\n[[Category:Castilian infantes]]\n[[Category:Counts of Barcelona]]\n[[Category:Counts of Burgundy]]\n[[Category:Counts of Charolais]]\n[[Category:Deaths from malaria]]\n[[Category:Dukes of Burgundy]]\n[[Category:Dukes of Milan]]\n[[Category:Dukes of Montblanc]]\n[[Category:Grand Masters of the Order of the Golden Fleece]]\n[[Category:Infectious disease deaths in Spain]]\n[[Category:Kings of Sicily]]\n[[Category:Knights of Santiago]]\n[[Category:Knights of the Garter]]\n[[Category:Knights of the Golden Fleece]]\n[[Category:Margrave